File: Emergency paramedics wearing a full COVID-19 coronavirus personal protective equipment (PPE) transfer an empty gurney to an ambulance at the Greenacres Hospital in Port Elizabeth. Pic: Marco Longari / AFP JOHANNESBURG - The health department reported 1,834 new COVID-19 cases in South Africa in the last 24 hours. This brings the total number of cases to 714,246. Level 1: Mkhize warns COVID-19 battle is not over There have been 53 additional COVID-19 deaths recorded, although only 20 of these occurred in the past 48 hours. South Africa's COVID-19 death toll has increased to 18,944. Recoveries currently stand at 644,641, which translates to a 90-percent recovery rate. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.